CHAPTER XXXII.

Division of the Roman Armies among the Consuls and Praetors. Arrangements for the Meetings of the Senate and the holding of the Courts of the Praetors. The Carthaginians hear of their Reverses in Spain. Hope of their being enabled to recover Sardinia. Mago sent to Italy with Troops and Supplics; Hasdrubal to Sardinia. At Rome the Consuls prepare to take the Field. Commands assigned to the Praetors and others—Rc. 215.
